Package org.omg.dds.sub

Interface DataReader.Selector<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The concrete type of the data to be read.
All Superinterfaces:
DDSObject
Enclosing interface:
DataReader<TYPE>
public static interface DataReader.Selector<T> extends DDSObject
Selector class encapsulates different ways of selecting samples from a DataReader. Selector can be used with DataReader.read(Selector) and DataReader.take(Selector) or it can be used stand-alone as it provides read() and take() functions. DataReader.select() creates a Selector that is bound to the DataReader. A Selector may encapsulate any combination of InstanceHandle, Subscriber.DataState, a query filter. It can be used to bound the maximum number of samples retrieved.
